TSHWANE - Tshwane Metro Police Department Chief Steven Ngobeni has resigned. Ngobeni is said to have stepped down following a discussion with executive mayor Solly Msimanga and the city manager, Moeketsi Mosola.READ: DA ready to create jobs in Tshwane: MsimangaThe mayoral spokesperson, Samkelo Mgobozi said the police chief and the city had agreed on the separation.Msimanga had called for Ngobeni to step down after his State of the Capital Address was disrupted a few weeks ago.At the time he accused the metro police chief of not taking action when this happened.Jenny Malan has been appointed acting police chief. eNCA